ing to Aguichine et al. (2021) models of irradiated ocean planets, but it could also be consistent with a gas dwarf scenario; that is, a dry Earth-like core surrounded by a substantial H/He envelope, as is inferred from atmospheric mass loss theories (Owen & Wu
